'''格罗·米森伯克'''（{{lang-de|'''Gero Miesenböck'''}}，{{bd|1965年|7月15日|}}），奥地利神经科学家，[[牛津大学|牛津大学]]韦恩弗利特生理学教授、神经回路和行为学中心主任，莫德林学院研究员。<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.cncb.ox.ac.uk/team/group-leaders/gero-miesenbock/ |title=存档副本 |accessdate=2013-10-30 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131102063126/http://www.cncb.ox.ac.uk/team/group-leaders/gero-miesenbock/ |archivedate=2013-11-02 }} Miesenböck’s research website at the University of Oxford</ref>

==生平==
他从[[因斯布鲁克大学|因斯布鲁克大学]]获医学博士学位并在[[詹姆斯·罗思曼|詹姆斯·罗思曼]]指导下进行博士后研究。来牛津之前，他曾在纪念[[斯隆-凯特琳癌症中心|斯隆-凯特琳癌症中心]]和[[耶鲁大学|耶鲁大学]]任职。<ref>{{cite journal|title=Patterns of synaptic activity in neural networks recorded by light emission from synaptolucins|pages=3402–3407|issn=0027-8424|journal=Proceedings of the National Academy of Sciences of the United States of America|volume=94|issue=7|date=1997-04-01|url=https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/9096406|accessdate=2019-02-12|author=G. Miesenböck, J. E. Rothman|pmid=9096406|pmc=PMC20382|archive-date=2013-11-01|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131101053100/http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/9096406|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|title=Visualizing secretion and synaptic transmission with pH-sensitive green fluorescent proteins|pages=192–195|issn=0028-0836|journal=Nature|volume=394|issue=6689|date=1998-07-09|doi=10.1038/28190|url=https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/9671304|accessdate=2019-02-12|author=G. Miesenböck, D. A. De Angelis, J. E. Rothman|pmid=9671304|archive-date=2019-12-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191205013632/https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/9671304|dead-url=no}}</ref>

米森伯克开创了现在被称为[[光遗传学|光遗传学]]的领域。<ref name=chARGe>{{cite journal|title=Selective photostimulation of genetically chARGed neurons|pages=15–22|issn=0896-6273|journal=Neuron|volume=33|issue=1|date=2002-01-03|url=https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/11779476|accessdate=2019-02-12|author=Boris V. Zemelman, Georgia A. Lee, Minna Ng, Gero Miesenböck|pmid=11779476|archive-date=2017-03-15|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170315135320/https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/11779476|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name=fly>{{cite journal|title=Remote control of behavior through genetically targeted photostimulation of neurons|pages=141–152|issn=0092-8674|journal=Cell|volume=121|issue=1|date=2005-04-08|doi=10.1016/j.cell.2005.02.004|url=https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/15820685|accessdate=2019-02-12|author=Susana Q. Lima, Gero Miesenböck|pmid=15820685|archive-date=2016-07-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160704025433/http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/15820685|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|title=Lighting up the brain|pages=52–59|issn=0036-8733|journal=Scientific American|volume=299|issue=4|date=2008-10|url=https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/18847085|accessdate=2019-02-12|author=Gero Miesenböck|pmid=18847085|archive-date=2013-11-01|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131101052012/http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/18847085|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|title=The optogenetic catechism|pages=395–399|issn=1095-9203|journal=Science (New York, N.Y.)|volume=326|issue=5951|date=2009-10-16|doi=10.1126/science.1174520|url=https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/19833960|accessdate=2019-02-12|author=Gero Miesenböck|pmid=19833960|archive-date=2013-11-01|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131101052203/http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/19833960|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name=TED>http://www.ted.com/talks/gero_miesenboeck.html {{Wayback|url=http://www.ted.com/talks/gero_miesenboeck.html |date=20140222021057 }} Miesenböck speaks at TED about optogenetics</ref>他是第一个从遗传上修改神经细胞，以使它们的电活动可以被光控制的科学家。<ref name=chARGe />这涉及编码光敏感视蛋白的DNA的植入。米森伯克使用了类似的遗传修饰来繁殖动物。这些动物的脑包含集成到它们的神经通路中的光敏感的细胞，第一次表明了这些动物的行为可被远程控制。<ref name=fly /><ref name=TED /><ref>{{cite news|last=Zimmer|first=Carl|title=An Off-or-On Switch for Controlling Animals?|url=http://www.nytimes.com/2005/04/12/science/12fly.html?pagewanted=print&position=&_r=0|accessdate=12 April 2005|newspaper=New York Times}}</ref>

